01:10:44,872 --> 01:10:47,741
"The punk who challenged me recklessly..."

2004
01:10:49,281 --> 01:10:52,111
(Kang Yang Cheol feels betrayed.)

2005
01:10:52,551 --> 01:10:54,120
"was my youngest grandson,"

2006
01:10:54,121 --> 01:10:57,491
(My youngest grandson)

2007
01:10:58,251 --> 01:10:59,261
"Jin Do Jun."

2008
01:10:59,961 --> 01:11:00,961
Yes?

2009
01:11:01,121 --> 01:11:02,291
(Jin Do Jun!)

2010
01:11:02,931 --> 01:11:04,460
- Yes? - Yes?

2011
01:11:04,461 --> 01:11:05,961
(He made it sound like he was calling Jin Do Jun.)

2012
01:11:07,631 --> 01:11:08,631
"Was it you?"

2013
01:11:09,731 --> 01:11:10,801
"Yes, Grandpa."

2014
01:11:13,471 --> 01:11:14,471
"Everything..."

2015
01:11:14,471 --> 01:11:15,471
(It's time to shout!)

2016
01:11:19,341 --> 01:11:20,341
Why...

2017
01:11:22,081 --> 01:11:23,081
Why...

2018
01:11:23,281 --> 01:11:25,350
(The shout gets stuck in his throat.)

2019
01:11:25,351 --> 01:11:27,681
- Keep going. - "Why?"

2020
01:11:28,651 --> 01:11:32,491
(He tries shouting again.)

2021
01:11:32,821 --> 01:11:34,791
"Why did you do such a thing?"

2022
01:11:35,561 --> 01:11:38,831
"Did you think that I'd give you Soonyang when you aren't even..."

2023
01:11:38,991 --> 01:11:40,001
"the oldest grandson?"

2024
01:11:40,131 --> 01:11:41,531
The last part was in sync.

2025
01:11:43,501 --> 01:11:44,571
"No, Grandpa."

2026
01:11:46,641 --> 01:11:47,741
"I'm going to buy it."

2027
01:11:48,801 --> 01:11:49,871
- "Soonyang." - My goodness.

2028
01:11:50,811 --> 01:11:53,481
(Delicate eyebrow movements)

2029
01:11:54,381 --> 01:11:55,381
"What?"

2030
01:11:57,151 --> 01:11:58,151
"What?"

2031
01:11:58,152 --> 01:12:02,080
(He stays focused on his performance until the end.)

2032
01:12:02,081 --> 01:12:03,590
- It got better with time. - Well done.

2033
01:12:03,591 --> 01:12:04,951
I can't break out of my character.

2034
01:12:07,321 --> 01:12:08,991
His accent...

2035
01:12:09,361 --> 01:12:10,860
It was perfect.

2036
01:12:10,861 --> 01:12:13,060
I used my accent in a natural way.

2037
01:12:13,061 --> 01:12:15,600
I think he did very well.

2038
01:12:15,601 --> 01:12:16,901
He did very well.

2039
01:12:17,271 --> 01:12:18,670
I had this thought.

2040
01:12:18,671 --> 01:12:23,271
I thought the video couldn't catch up to his voice.

2041
01:12:23,671 --> 01:12:25,840
It was so nice.

2042
01:12:25,841 --> 01:12:27,211
- You're too kind. - Yes. It was...

2043
01:12:29,181 --> 01:12:32,280
It started out like a joke,

2044
01:12:32,281 --> 01:12:34,250
but he was absorbed in emotions.

2045
01:12:34,251 --> 01:12:35,251
- Seriously. - In the middle, he sounded like...

2046
01:12:35,251 --> 01:12:36,251
- he was reading a book. - Yes.

2047
01:12:36,252 --> 01:12:37,851
I think you lack good judgment.

2048
01:12:39,291 --> 01:12:44,591
(He read the long lines instead of delivering them.)

2049
01:12:44,691 --> 01:12:46,430
- "Did you think that..." - I know.

2050
01:12:46,431 --> 01:12:48,860
"You made me buy Hando Steel at a high price..."

2051
01:12:48,861 --> 01:12:50,300
- I thought... - "And..."

2052
01:12:50,301 --> 01:12:52,400
that he took liberty with the dubbing.

2053
01:12:52,401 --> 01:12:53,540
He took liberty with the dubbing. How cool.

2054
01:12:53,541 --> 01:12:54,670
He loved it.

2055
01:12:54,671 --> 01:12:56,140
He's very good at using the head voice.

2056
01:12:56,141 --> 01:12:57,740
Now, it's time...

2057
01:12:57,741 --> 01:13:00,911
to announce the best one among the seven interviewees.

2058
01:13:01,281 --> 01:13:04,281
The one who got picked as the rookie voice actor...

2059
01:13:04,651 --> 01:13:06,521
of Brother School's Radio Club is...

2060
01:13:06,781 --> 01:13:08,150
Who is it?

2061
01:13:08,151 --> 01:13:09,351
(The aspiring voice actors are desperate.)

2062
01:13:09,851 --> 01:13:12,990
Kang Ho Dong!

2063
01:13:12,991 --> 01:13:14,521
Kang Ho Dong!

2064
01:13:15,061 --> 01:13:16,290
Why?

2065
01:13:16,291 --> 01:13:17,430
- Why? - "Why?"

2066
01:13:17,431 --> 01:13:19,431
- I mean... - Hello.

2067
01:13:19,801 --> 01:13:22,100
His explosive performance was great when he played Jin Yang Cheol.

2068
01:13:22,101 --> 01:13:23,630
The moment his name got written down,

2069
01:13:23,631 --> 01:13:24,670
- everyone said, - That's right.

2070
01:13:24,671 --> 01:13:26,100
"That's right."

2071
01:13:26,101 --> 01:13:28,540
"You made me buy Hando Steel at a high price!"

2072
01:13:28,541 --> 01:13:29,511
That part was lacking. The ending was nice.

2073
01:13:29,512 --> 01:13:31,111
"And depleted the group's money reserves."

2074
01:13:31,571 --> 01:13:34,140
- He's absorbed. - JTBC's first voice actor.

2075
01:13:34,141 --> 01:13:35,511
- "Jin Do Jun." - Kang Ho Dong.

2076
01:13:36,151 --> 01:13:37,180
"Was it you?"

2077
01:13:37,181 --> 01:13:39,080
All right. How was it to be on the show today?

2078
01:13:39,081 --> 01:13:40,951
Please take turns to answer.

2079
01:13:41,181 --> 01:13:45,551
Being on Men on a Mission made me think,

2080
01:13:45,751 --> 01:13:48,121
"The show lives up to its name."

2081
01:13:48,521 --> 01:13:49,990
I felt honored.

2082
01:13:49,991 --> 01:13:52,191
- It was nice to meet everyone. - Clap.

2083
01:13:52,461 --> 01:13:56,230
I'm preparing for a performance.

2084
01:13:56,231 --> 01:13:59,300
I want to make a foundation...

2085
01:13:59,301 --> 01:14:01,040
that'll give donations...

2086
01:14:01,041 --> 01:14:03,470
to children in need.

2087
01:14:03,471 --> 01:14:06,510
If there are people who want to join me for the cause,

2088
01:14:06,511 --> 01:14:09,680
please contact me through my Instagram account.

2089
01:14:09,681 --> 01:14:12,080
- That's nice. - I'll be very grateful...

2090
01:14:12,081 --> 01:14:13,680
- if you do that. - Okay.

2091
01:14:13,681 --> 01:14:14,681
That's nice.

2092
01:14:14,682 --> 01:14:16,420
Although I visited the show as well,

2093
01:14:16,421 --> 01:14:18,220
these three voice actors...

2094
01:14:18,221 --> 01:14:21,221
and the members were the ones I only watched from afar.

2095
01:14:21,561 --> 01:14:23,930
Today, I became a part of that dream.

2096
01:14:23,931 --> 01:14:26,030
I made the happiest memories.

2097
01:14:26,031 --> 01:14:27,930
- Thank you. - Good luck.

2098
01:14:27,931 --> 01:14:30,100
We could show what voice actors were like,

2099
01:14:30,101 --> 01:14:32,770
so it was fun and meaningful.

2100
01:14:32,771 --> 01:14:35,440
Please give a lot of love to the voice actors of Korea.

2101
01:14:35,441 --> 01:14:37,771
(Please give a lot of love to the voice actors of Korea.)

2102
01:14:38,071 --> 01:14:42,651
We'll remember your voices forever.
